Great idea — a soft transition will make the project feel like one continuous space rather than two stacked panels.  
The simplest approach is to keep the overall palette identical and use a fade at the bottom of the hero section that blends into the body’s paper‑tone. You can do this with a gradient and a short keyframe animation:

```css
.hero {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  justify-content: center;
  align-items: center;
  height: 60vh;
  background-image:
    linear-gradient(to bottom, rgba(253,252,248,0) 80%, #fdfcf8 100%),
